description.narrative: A national framework for Life Skills and Citizenship Education (LSCE) based education including teachers’ tools for curricular and co-curricular was developed and experimented in 30 lower secondary schools and 28 second chance schools (SCS) benefiting more than 22000 children in 2021. LSCE framework was augmented including Upshift programs in 2021 both within second chance schools and youth centres benefiting 416 Adolescents and youth.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
